m to be a highly skilled craftsman. This first full-length study of his life and works presents a critical assessment of the man and his music, setting him within the social and religious context of the so-called Counter-Reformation. Beginning by outlining the facts of his life, the book goes on to offer an analysis and assessment of his output. Clive Walkley was until his retirement a lecturer in music and music education at Lancaster University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aChurch musicxCatholic Churchy17th century. 0aChurch musicy17th centuryzSpain. 0aChurch musiczSpainy17th century. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aHistory of Religion. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aCounter-Reformation.  aJuan Esquivel.  aMarian antiphons.  aSpanish musical life.  aearly seventeenth centuries.  ahymns.  alate sixteenth.  amagnificats.  amasses.  amotets.  apsalms.  areligious context.  asacred polyphony.  asocial.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846159053423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846159053/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles